📜 Beschreibung 》
Shizuka ist eine normale Oberschülerin, die Geister sehen kann und sie magisch anzuziehen scheint. Weil das allein ziemlich gefährlich ist, arbeitet sie als Assistentin für den berühmten Spirituellen Kamui. Der ist zwar extrem selbstsicher, doch seine Methode, Geister auszutreiben, ist alles andere als gewöhnlich. Zusammen geraten die beiden immer wieder in bizarre, übernatürliche Situationen.

But putting that all into a single interface really misses the point of doctoring.

Emily: Exactly. And this is back to that same, “Oh, it’s better than nothing,” right? It’s like, well, why was the alternative nothing? Why can’t we actually get our act together and kick the for-profit health insurers and also the private equity out of health care, and then redirect those resources? There’s lots that could be done. "A blue jay bursts through the crepe myrtle branches in a moment that feels both swift and deliberate, as if the bird has slipped into a narrow doorway of light. Its wings are fully spread, each feather catching the sun in soft gradients of blue, gray, and charcoal. The body tilts slightly forward, giving the sense of a bird threading its way through a living maze.

Around it, the crepe myrtle is lush and textured—clusters of bright pink blossoms glowing like small lanterns, leaves shining in layered greens, and tight beads of unripe berries tucked among the branches. The foliage forms a kind of natural tunnel, dense yet dappled with light, and the jay’s flight seems to part it for just an instant. The contrast between the bird’s cool blue tones and the warm, vivid colors of the tree makes the moment feel electric, as if the jay is carrying a piece of sky through a garden." - Microsoft Copilot
